<P>
   KOSOVO-U.S. (Washington) _ The Senate is expected to vote
Thursday on a July 2001 deadline for withdrawing American ground
troops from Kosovo. The legislation is an $8.6 billion military
construction measure, which also carries $4.7 billion for U.S.
operations in Kosovo, anti-drug efforts in Colombia and other
defense programs that have been labeled emergency spending. By Eric
Schmitt.
</P>
<P>
   With
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-BUSH (Washington) _ Exploring the tension between George
W. Bush's internationalist leanings and the congressional
Republican leadership on Kosovo, fast-track and, to a lesser
extent, China trade.
</P>
<P>
   CHINA-TRADE (Washington) _ Developments on the China trade bill
pending in Congress. By Joseph Kahn.
</P>
<P>
   ETHIOPIA-ERITREA (Dateline to kum) _ Ethiopia captures a key
town in Eritrea; 200,000 people flee. By Ian Fisher.
</P>
<P>
   With
</P>
<P>
   ETHIOPIA-ERITREA-U.N. (United Nations) _ The Security Council
has imposed an arms embargo on Ethiopia and Eritrea in the hope
that it will spur the two sides toward a resumption of peace talks.
By Barbara Crossette.
</P>
<P>
   SIERRA-LEONE (Freetown) _ Developments in the wake of the
capture of the rebel leader. By Norimitsu Onishi.
</P>
<P>
   GENE-ALTERED-FOOD (Paris) _ Anger is expressed in Europe at the
news that some genetically modified seeds accidentally imported
from Canada have been unwittingly used by farmers. By Donald G.
McNeil Jr.
</P>
<P>
   DOMINICAN-ELECTION (Santo Domingo, Dominican Republic) _
Developments in the presidential election: Does leftist challenger
have a majority? By David Gonzalez.
</P>
