<SLUG> BC-HISPANIC-VOTERS-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;     GOP OFFICIAL SEES HISPANICS AS MAKING DIFFERENCE IN MIDWEST 
</HEADLINE>
   &HT;     (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 &HT;     By MATT FLORES  
 &HT;     c.2000 San Antonio Express-News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAN ANTONIO _ Hispanic voters, specifically those in the
Midwest, may be the deciding factor in who becomes the next
president, said the chairman of the Republican Party of Florida.
</P>
<P>
   ``Every single state in the Midwest is in play, and Hispanic
voters in those states may well make the difference in who controls
the Electoral College in the presidential election,'' said Al
Cardenas, who also is a Republican National Committee member.
</P>
<P>
   Cardenas made his comments Wednesday during a luncheon of the
Republican National Hispanic Assembly of Texas, an outreach
committee whose mission is to recruit Hispanics into the party.
</P>
<P>
   Noting that Texas Gov. George W. Bush holds leads in the South
and in some Western states, and that Vice President Al Gore enjoys
stronger backing in the Northeast and in other Western states,
Cardenas said the Midwest could be key in determining who becomes
president.
</P>
<P>
   Bush, the Republican presidential hopeful, and Gore, a Democrat,
are in statistical dead heats in virtually all Midwest states, and
Hispanic voters represent enough of the electorate in each of the
states to swing the vote in either direction, Cardenas said.
</P>
<P>
   With a campaign theme that emphasizes education, Cardenas said,
the Republican Party is hoping its message will resonate with
Hispanics.
</P>
<P>
   ``We believe we have the one issue that transcends all politics
... and education is going to be our legacy and entry into minority
politics,'' Cardenas said.
</P>
<P>
   ``If you are going to do well in the Hispanic community, you
have to deliver financial resources and good issues, and you have
to recruit good candidates,'' he added.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (Contact Matt Flores by e-mail at mflores(at)express-news.net)
</P>
</TEXT>
