<SLUG> BC-GETAWAY-BEACHES17-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Six family-friendly beaches with laid-back latitude
 &HT;    By Paula Crouch Thrasher
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Few Southeastern beaches retain the '60s charm of a Tybee
Island. But when you think of affordable seaside spots that haven't
been swallowed up by wall-to-wall high-rises, there are more
options.
</P>
<P>
   With Memorial Day weekend and the start of the summer-in-the-sun
season, you may be looking for just such a place.
</P>
<P>
   Here are some family-friendly beaches where you'll fit right in
with your flip-flops and cutoffs:
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Jekyll Island: Bicycling, golfing, tennis, fishing, boating
and beachcombing fill your days at this state-owned beach. Jekyll
Island Authority, 1-877-453-5955; www.jekyllisland.com.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Gulf Shores, Ala.: Kids will love Adventure Island, where
there's minigolf, laser tag, paddle boats, roller coaster
simulator, NASCAR simulator, 100 arcade games and go-cart
supertrack. But don't pass up the beauty of the 6,000-acre Bon
Secour National Wildlife Refuge. Gulf Shores Orange Beach,
1-800-745-7263; www.gulfshores.com.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Pensacola, Fla.: The Gulf Island National Seashore keeps white
sand beaches accessible to the public. While there are plenty of
places to stay and eat, there are also stretches of delightfully
undeveloped shoreline. Santa Rosa Island Authority, 1-800-635-4803;
www.visitpensacola.com.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  St. Augustine Beach, Fla.: Four miles of shoreline await at
Anastasia State Recreation Area, where you can also enjoy camping,
fishing, boating and surfing. Several moderately priced hotels and
lots of condo rentals are nearby. St. John's County Convention and
Visitors Bureau, 1-800-653-2489; www.visitoldcity.com.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Melbourne Beach, Fla: Established in 1883, this is Brevard
County's oldest beach community. The Space Coast destination boasts
nesting sea turtles. Plus, it's convenient to the Kennedy Space
Center, the Canaveral National Seashore and Merritt Island National
Wildlife Refuge. 1-800-771-9922; www.melpb-chamber.org.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Folly Beach, S.C.: Just 15 minutes from downtown Charleston,
this barrier island abounds with rare birds, history, fishing and
only one oceanfront motel. Charleston Area Convention &AMP; Visitors
Bureau, 1-800-774-0006; www.charlestoncvb.com.
</P>
<P>
   Paula Crouch Thrasher writes for the Atlanta
Journal-Constitution.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
