<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Southern happenings
 &HT;    By Paula Crouch Thrasher
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QR;  Macon, Ga. _ ``Mysteries of Egypt'' opens Friday at the Museum
of Arts and Sciences with a collection of 300 artifacts. Visitors
will learn about King Tutankhamen's tomb, how the Pyramids were
built and view Egyptian mummies. Through July 9. 912-477-3232;
www.masmacon.com.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Rome, Ga. _ Mayfest on the Rivers on Saturday celebrates the
city's three rivers with free riverboat rides on a 48-passenger
excursion boat, the Corrugated Mad River run, and a concert
featuring Percy Sledge and Three Dog Night. 706-295-5576,
www.romegeorgia.com.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Hiawassee, Ga. _ The annual Rhododendron Festival at the
Georgia Mountain Fair grounds is Friday through Sunday and May
26-28. The event includes music, arts and crafts and concerts by
Diamond Rio and Trace Adkins (May 27). More than 3,000 plants bloom
from early April through late May along a mile-long, pine-bark
trail on the shore of Lake Chatuge. 706-896-4191;
www.georgia-mountain-fair.com.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Gatlinburg, Tenn. _ The Gatlinburg Scottish Festival and Games
is Friday through Sunday in Mills Park. Features Highland and
country dancing, Scottish heavy athletics, pipe bands, border
collies, more than 50 clan tents and Scottish vendors.
865-457-8242.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Rugby, Tenn. _ The 26th annual Festival of British and
Appalachian Culture, Saturday and Sunday, includes music and
dancing, traditional arts and craftspeople demonstrating and
selling their work, storytelling, historic building tours and food.
423-628-2441.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Ocoee, Tenn. _ American Whitewater presents the 16th annual
Ocoee Whitewater Rodeo, Friday through Sunday, on the Upper Ocoee.
More than 200 competitors from around the world are expected in
kayak and canoe categories. Plus, vendor booths, food and
entertainment. 828-645-5299.
</P>
<P>
   _Paula Crouch Thrasher writes for the Atlanta
Journal-Constitution.
</P>
