<HEADLINE>
NELSON EXCITED ABOUT COACHING MAVS AGAIN
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By DWAIN PRICE 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   DALLAS _ Don Nelson returned to his Reunion Arena office
Thursday after vacationing in Hawaii and said he'll probably
finalize a deal with owner Mark Cuban soon to coach the Dallas
Mavericks again next season.
</P>
<P>
   Cuban, who is vacationing in London and plans to return to
Dallas late this month, said Wednesday that Nelson is his only
candidate to coach the team next season.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm just really excited about this team,'' Nelson said
Thursday. ``I don't think anybody can coach them better than I can.
Mark seems to want me to come back, and I'm leaning that way. I
think it's just a matter of us getting together more than
anything.''
</P>
<P>
   Nelson had said he would retire from coaching after this season,
but Cuban's persuasion and overwhelming support from key players
convinced Nelson he should return.
</P>
<P>
   ``When you start looking for people, it's not easy to find a
good coach,'' Nelson said. ``There's about five or six teams
looking for a coach.''
</P>
<P>
   The Mavericks closed the season with an impressive 16-5 record
in their last 21 games. They were 40-42 overall, four games behind
Sacramento in the race for the final Western Conference playoff
spot.
</P>
<P>
   Like Cuban, Nelson wants to build on that momentum, saying the
prospects of advancing to the playoffs next season is ``one of the
reasons I want to stay.''
</P>
<P>
   Nelson is under contract to continue as the Mavericks' general
manager for the next three seasons. PARKER RETURNS
</P>
<P>
   Charlie Parker, the only one of Don Nelson's nine assistant
coaches who doesn't have a contract, will get another deal soon,
Nelson said.
</P>
<P>
   Nelson had said Parker, Del Harris, Donnie Nelson and Sidney
Moncrief would be his ``bench coaches'' during games next season.
But NBA rules permit only three assistants on the bench.
</P>
<P>
   ``We'll figure that out,'' Don Nelson said. ``But those guys are
going to be with me. I'm not going to have any titles with the
assistants on the bench. We're just going to be coaches.''
</P>
<P>
   Scott Roth, a bench assistant last season, is now an advance
scout for the Mavericks. JONES LIKELY GONE
</P>
<P>
   Guard Damon Jones' career with the Mavericks appears to be over
because Dallas has Michael Finley, Steve Nash, Greg Buckner, Hubert
Davis, Erick Strickland and possibly Robert Pack on board in the
backcourt.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's going to be hard for Damon to make our team next year,''
Don Nelson said. ``So we told Damon that he should look around for
another team.'' nn
</P>
</TEXT>
