   COUNCIL-POWERGRAB (Los Angeles) _ In a brazen bid to circumvent
the new, voter-approved city charter, the City Council is set to
consider an ordinance Friday that would restore power to Ron
Deaton, the city's chief legislative analyst and the most powerful
person in Los Angeles municipal government. The ordinance would
strip the mayor of his role as chief negotiator with state and
federal governments. Mayor Richard Riordan is lobbying council
members to vote against the ordinance. By Alexa Haussler. (Will
move in the ``a'' national and ``n'' California news files.)
