<P>
   ATTENTION GRAPHICS EDITORS:
</P>
<P>
   We have moved a stand-alone graphics package on tornadoes,
produced by Gentry J. Sleets of The N.Y. Times News Service. These
graphics are for use as needed and can help illustrate recent
stories on tornado activity.
</P>
<P>
   The package consists of the following:
</P>
<P>
   1: TORNADO--Formation -- 2 x 10 -- (BC-TORNADO-FORMATION)
</P>
<P>
   Outlines the meteorological forces involved in the formation of
a tornado.
</P>
<P>
   2: TORNADO--Fujita -- 6 x 3 -- (BC-TORNADO-FUJITA)
</P>
<P>
   Illustrates the Fujita scale which is used to calculate a
tornado's level of
</P>
<P>
   destruction.
</P>
<P>
   3: TORNADO--Preparation -- 4 x 4 -- (BC-TORNADO-READINESS)
</P>
<P>
   Safety tips on what to do if there is a tornado alert.
</P>
<P>
   4: TORNADO--Deaths -- 1 x 5 (BC- TORNADO-DEATHS)
</P>
<P>
   Outlines the numbers of tornadoes and deaths in the U.S. since
1950.
</P>
<P>
   5: TORNADO--Map -- 2 x tk -- (BC-TORNADO-MAP)
</P>
<P>
   Where tornadoes tend to strike in the U.S.
</P>
