<SLUG> BC-CORRECTIONS-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR FRIDAY, MAY 19
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Friday. Days and dates refer to the original article's transmission
by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be adjusted by
NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-WORLD-BRIEFS-NYT (moved on Wednesday, May 17)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Wednesday, May 17,
about a plan to build a high-technology industrial park in Hong
Kong misstated the projected cost. It is $2 billion, not $2
million.
</P>
<P>
   BC-SCI-SPACE-STATION-NYT (moved on Monday, May 15)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Monday, May 15,
about efforts to keep the International Space Station in its orbit
misstated the effects of the atmosphere on its descent. As the
space station loses altitude it speeds up, it does not slow down.
</P>
<P>
   The article also referred incorrectly to the pressure of the
atmosphere at the space station's orbit, about 200 miles high. That
pressure is higher than that created by modern vacuum pumps on
earth, not lower.
</P>
<P>
   BC-CIR-GEEK-NOTES-NYT (moved on Wednesday, May 17)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Wednesday, May 17,
about the discovery of what may be a rare photograph of the poet
Emily Dickinson included two sentences erroneously merged in
editing. The error produced an incorrect reference to Dr. Philip
Gura, professor of American literature and culture at the
University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill. Dr. Gura, who bought
the photograph on the eBay auction site, is not a forensic
anthropologist and is not the person who will try to determine the
photograph's authenticity.
</P>
<P>
   BC-CIR-GEEK-NOTES-NYT (moved on Wednesday, May 17)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Wednesday, May 17,
about an Internet dictation service, iDictate.com, misstated the
telephone number. It is (877) 342-8283.
</P>
<P>
   BC-HIRSCHFELD-DEALER-NYT (moved on Tuesday, May 16)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Tuesday, May 16,
about a lawsuit by the artist Al Hirschfeld against his dealer,
Margo Feiden Galleries, referred imprecisely to its payments to
him. The contract stipulated that the gallery owner, Feiden, must
pay Hirschfeld an annual minimum of $12,000 if the contract was to
be renewed. Her payments this year have been more than that sum,
not equal to it.
</P>
<P>
   BC-RESTAURANT-PRICES-NYT (moved on Tuesday, May 16)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Tuesday, May 16,
about rising prices in Manhattan restaurants misstated the cost of
the prix fixe menu at Jean Georges. It is $85, not $125.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
